flowchart LR
  subgraph Clients[Clients and operator surfaces]
    B[Browser client]
    N[Native app client]
    A[Admin and operator UI]
    API[External API consumers]
  end

  FE[Front-end / API gateway]

  B --> FE
  N --> FE
  A --> FE
  API --> FE

  subgraph ACP[The Agentic Control Plane]
    UM[User management / auth]
    ST[Session and thread management]
    TW[Task and workload management]
    AD[Agent directory]
    MB[Message bus / eventing]
    SM[State management / datastore]
    PS[Persistence and storage]
  end

  FE --> ACP

  subgraph SEC[Security, governance, and compliance]
    RBAC[RBAC / ABAC]
    AUDIT[Audit / logging]
    SECRETS[Secrets management]
    OBS[Observability]
    POLICY[Policy engine]
    DG[Data governance]
  end

  subgraph INT[Integrations and adaptors]
    CHAT[Slack / Teams / chat]
    COMMS[Email / SMS / voice]
    CAL[Calendar / docs]
    SYS[CRM / ERP / databases]
    RPA[RPA / browsers / legacy]
    IOT[IoT / robotics]
  end

  subgraph CAP[Capabilities and execution]
    SKILL[Skill registry]
    WF[Workflows / automation]
    RULES[Rules / expert systems]
    MODELS[ML / AI models]
    WORKERS[Agent workers]
    TOOLS[APIs and tools]
  end

  ACP --> INT
  ACP --> CAP
  SEC -. guards .-> ACP
  SEC -. governs .-> INT
  SEC -. constrains .-> CAP
